dd
•	Purpose: Bit-by-bit disk imaging
•	Type: CLI
•	Notes: Basic tool, no built-in forensic safeguards

dc3dd
•	Purpose: Enhanced forensic imaging
•	Type: CLI
•	Notes:
•	Built-in hashing (MD5/SHA)
•	Error handling and logging
•	Preferred over dd for forensics

Guymager
•	Purpose: GUI-based disk imaging
•	Type: GUI
•	Notes:
•	Supports E01, AFF, RAW formats
•	Built-in hashing and logging
•	Fast and easy to use

    ---Cross Platform---

The Sleuth Kit (TSK)
•	Purpose: Disk image analysis
•	Type: CLI
•	Notes:
•	Supports FAT, NTFS, EXT
•	Tools: fls, icat, tsk_recover
•	Ideal for scripting

Autopsy
•	Purpose: GUI disk analysis
•	Type: GUI
•	Notes:
•	Frontend for TSK
•	Timeline, keyword search, carving
•	Supports plugins

Bulk Extractor
•	Purpose: Data extraction
•	Type: CLI
•	Notes:
•	Extracts emails, URLs, patterns
•	Works without file system parsing